				Maven Steps

Maven co-ordinates:
groupId (package name e.g com.xyz)
artifactId (Proj Name)
packaging
version (from snapshot to prod)

Phases: Process-resource --> compile --> test --> package (jar, war)

Maven Installation:

setx MAVEN_HOME "C:\Program Files\ApacheFoundation\apache-maven-3.3.9"
setx M2_HOME "C:\Program Files\ApacheFoundation\apache-maven-3.3.9"
setx path "C:\Program Files\ApacheFoundation\apache-maven-3.3.9\bin"
set MAVEN_OPTS=-Xms256m
set MAVEN_OPTS=Xms256m -Xmx512m

groupId, artifactId & version can be verified from "repo.maven.apache.org/maven2"

* dependeny will be accessed from "repo.maven.apache.org/maven2"
* It also verify first from local system (local maven repository folder on your machine under .m2)
* Can be checked from Enterprise lib

<settings>
    <proxies>
        <proxy>
            <id>company-main-proxy</id>
            <active>true</active>
            <protocol>http</protocol>
            <host>proxy host</host>
            <port>80</port>
            <nonProxyHosts>localhost|*.corpintra.net</nonProxyHosts>
        </proxy>
        <proxy>
           <id>company-main-proxy</id>
            <active>true</active>
            <protocol>https</protocol>
            <host>proxy host</host>
            <port>80</port>
            <nonProxyHosts>localhost|*.corpintra.net</nonProxyHosts>
        </proxy>
    </proxies>
</settings>

Transitive Dependency:
Maven can download the dependency transitively

Maven Scope:
scope
compile (by default build, test and run)
runtime (test, run)
provided (test, run)
test (compile, test)
system
